  <div class="pdia-grid">
    <div class="pdia-card">
      <div class="pdia-letter">P</div>
      <div class="pdia-title">Problem Construction</div>
      <div class="pdia-tagline">Define the real problem, not symptoms</div>
      <ul class="pdia-list">
        <li>The problem is not "bad AQI data." It is that Lahore residents face a public health emergency 10 months a year with no clear government accountability mechanism.</li>
        <li>Who authorises action? There is no clear problem owner across PEPA, Punjab Environmental Protection, Agriculture, Transport, and Health ministries.</li>
        <li>The data exists, but it is not connected to decisions: a monitoring-action gap.</li>
        <li>Citizens have no real-time access or transparent health advisories tied to this data.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="pdia-card">
      <div class="pdia-letter">D</div>
      <div class="pdia-title">Diagnose Causes</div>
      <div class="pdia-tagline">Fishbone the drivers before jumping to solutions</div>
      <ul class="pdia-list">
        <li>Institutional: fragmented mandate across 5+ agencies, no single authoriser for smog response.</li>
        <li>Technical: single-station monitoring, PM2.5-only, no source apportionment, 13% data missing.</li>
        <li>Political economy: brick kiln owners, trucking lobbies, and large farm operators resist regulation.</li>
        <li>Behavioural: farmers burn crop residue because alternatives (happy seeders, bio-decomposers) are not subsidised at scale.</li>
        <li>Transboundary: shared airsheds with Indian Punjab; no bilateral coordination mechanism exists.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="pdia-card">
      <div class="pdia-letter">I</div>
      <div class="pdia-title">Iterate and Explore</div>
      <div class="pdia-tagline">Small experiments, not big plans</div>
      <ul class="pdia-list">
        <li>Deploy 3 additional low-cost sensors (PurpleAir or AirQino) in industrial, traffic-dense, and residential zones to test spatial variation cheaply before investing in a full network.</li>
        <li>Pilot a real-time public dashboard in one district with SMS-based health alerts; measure behaviour change before scaling.</li>
        <li>Run a small incentive scheme for crop-residue alternatives in 2 tehsils; evaluate the AQI signal before expanding.</li>
        <li>Convene a monthly inter-ministerial data review to create an accountability ritual before restructuring mandates.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="pdia-card">
      <div class="pdia-letter">A</div>
      <div class="pdia-title">Authorisers and Action</div>
      <div class="pdia-tagline">Who needs to move, and what do they need to act?</div>
      <ul class="pdia-list">
        <li>The Chief Minister's office needs to designate a single "smog coordinator" with cross-ministry authority during the October – February smog season.</li>
        <li>The Agriculture Department needs AQI data integrated into its crop calendar advisories.</li>
        <li>Punjab EPA needs enforcement data (kiln closures, factory shutdowns) linked to AQI monitoring to demonstrate impact.</li>
        <li>International donors (USAID, GIZ, EU) need a compelling data narrative; this dataset is that starting point.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

